translated: Örn, Carl Henrik Gunnar, senior physician, general practitioner, doctor, Linköping, b. 30/10/06 in Karlstad to regimental doctor Elis Ö. and Thérèse Uggla. Married in 1942 to Sif Ahrén. Children: Claes Henrik b. 1943, Eva b. 1945. Completed high school in Linköping in 1925, obtained a Bachelor of Medicine degree in 1929, and a Medical License in 1934 in Stockholm. Held several short-term appointments and served as an assistant physician at the medical department of Linköping County Hospital from 1934-1940, at Orup Sanatorium in 1936-1937, at the Stockholm Epidemic Hospital from 1941-1944, and at the Samaritan Children's Hospital in 1944. Served as a naval doctor in the Naval Reserve from 1937, with military appointments from 1937-1944. Became the chief physician at the Central Epidemic Hospital in Linköping in 1945. Studied abroad in 1938 and 1946.
